---
/**
 * "My On-Time Promise" — Chris's trust statement, in a warm-gray band that
 * echoes the original site's gray palette (#edebe8 / #615a5a). Subtle by
 * design (no big buttons) so it builds trust without competing with the
 * page's primary CTA.
 */
import Icon from "./Icon.astro";
---

<section style="background-color:#edebe8">
  <div class="container-page py-12 md:py-16">
    <div class="flex flex-col sm:flex-row gap-5 sm:gap-7 max-w-3xl">
      <span
        class="inline-flex items-center justify-center w-12 h-12 rounded-2xl shrink-0 text-white"
        style="background-color:#615a5a"
      >
        <Icon name="clock" class="w-6 h-6" />
      </span>
      <div>
        <span class="eyebrow text-navy-500">My on-time promise</span>
        <h2 class="mt-2 text-2xl md:text-3xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-navy-900">
          Time and trust go together
        </h2>
        <p class="mt-3 text-lg text-navy-700 leading-relaxed">
          If we agree on a time frame, I'll be there at that time. If something
          outside my control changes, you'll hear from me right away, and we'll
          work with you to set an updated appointment. You'll never be left
          wondering whether I'm showing up — or just late. I respect your home and
          your schedule, and I'll leave your home cleaner than when I started.
        </p>
        <p class="mt-4 text-navy-600">
          — Chris Wise, Owner ·
          <a href="/about" class="text-gulf-700 link-underline font-medium">why I started Wise Residential</a>
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
